caption: Best fried chicken sandwich ever!! Chicken is so soft and tender, it melts in your mouth while the batter is crunchy and crispy! Everything else on the menu was super delicious and they had great selection of organic wines. Other favorites were the flatbread w. hummus and stuffed flank steak. Overall, I was happy with the service and the quality of food. I would highly recommend!

Hidden gem in Brooklyn. Food and service were top notch. We tried almost everything on the menu including fried chicken sandwich, matbucha hummus and stuffed flank steak all of which were delicious. The organic wine selection was great as well. Would love to revisit soon!
Ordered the chicken sandwich which was good but it was the pink peppercorn tapenade that blew me away & the homemade salted chips that came with - SO delicious! Please do all day, not just after 2pm.

I ordered two breakfast sandwiches and a few pastries.  The chicken sandwich was over sauced and the ratio of meat to bun was out of whack.  The choice of bun was also careless and very dry.  The spice mixture in the sausage resembled not middle eastern food but more of a late night watered dumbed down Indian curry powder.  The bread pudding was flavorful but was ice cold , I’d prefer it at least tempered if not warm.  The spinach “croissant” is not a croissant, it’s a galette, which was also refrigerator temperature.  I rarely review, and after spending 60 dollars at this establishment, It is my ethical duty to warn the public about this.  The devil is in the details and this place falls short on all levels.  Pandemic or not, we are better than this people.
Best coffee!
Kind of pricey for the neighborhood, but solid food! It's a small space, so might not be easy to get a seat during popular times.

Indoor dining is now available, in addition to outdoor dining. Seating inside is limited but if you're lucky enough like we were to snag a table before the weekend brunch crowd, you'll be in for a treat. Lovely interior with plants and cute decor, even their coffee cups add nice flair. Nice options for breakfast. Seems small but our food was hearty and perfectly filling. Pastries look yummy, was tempted by their bread pudding from banana foster bread. Everything we had was yummy. Service was great. Star of the show was whiskey latte, I will say  can't go wrong with anything here. Central location off Fulton St but still has a chill, quaint, out of city vibes.
The dinner for two is amazing! Thank you!
Way overpriced, rude staff.
Specialty drinks are fire
Holiday donut is a contender!
yum, go here now

Golda breakfasts used to be our family tradition before COVID until we moved away from the neighborhood. Beef bacon on that breakfast sandwich was fantastic. Fun breakfast options all around. Seating is limited but not impossible to score if you wait a bit. Most tables are tiny and good for two people but there is one larger one for a slightly larger group.
Fresh, good, cool and so tasty. Nothing fancy here just good food.
Killer fried chicken sandwich.  It held up well when I hate the second half later that afternoon, too.
Golda serves high-quality foods, and their sandwiches are made with the best breads and ingredients. I especially enjoy their fluffy egg sandwiches.

Do not order from this place! They only delivered half my order, food is horrible (eggs were microwaved) and customer service when I called to let them know about all of this was not the best. Spend your money elsewhere that can give you at least basic quality food and service.
Super impressed with this place! Food was excellent and the gentleman behind the bar was friendly & accommodating. Highly reccomend!
SO cute and yummy. Chicken sandwich is ridiculously good and new pomegranate salad is somethin special. The shrub watermelon vinegar drink also delicious!! Staff and chefs super nice as well :)
The cauliflower is excellent!
the food is great, but it's super expensive (especially for the area), and there isn't enough seating
Great little spot. Had breakfast here and both food and beverages were well crafted. Will definitely come back to try other things.
Great little find in the neighborhood. Cool vibe, delicious breakfast
Excellent selection of Espresso beverages, happy and energetic staff. The food is delicious and A1 if you're ever in the area and would like a delicious breakfast this is the spot to head too !

An tiny cozy all-day Mediterranean eatery with nicely presented yummy food and Mediterranean inspired beverage. We enjoyed the cauliflower dish. Tabbouleh salad was simply great with vinegar dressing. They are serving coffee beans from Parlor roastery and often change the food menu too.

Got our brunch order wrong, deep fried potatoes left a pool of grease behind. Toast was great, eggs over medium were good (but were ordered scrambled). Overall not bad, but expected more, especially from a place where you tip up front when you order.

Have had two brunch sandwiches and the vegan pastries at Golda and through and through there was not a bad bite to be had.  Amazingly soft bread on the sandwiches was a highlight, when so many rolls are just an afterthought. The ingredients therein were plentiful, flavorful, and paired excellently. Saucy, yolky, perfection. These are must-have sandwiches.  The vegan pumpkin muffin was a good appetizer - so soft and chewy, it could also serve for dessert.
Good place for breakfast, a little pricy but dishes are above standard.

I got coffee and an egg sandwich -- I would get coffee here again but egg sandwich was nasty and over priced, roll seemed old and bacon was cold. youre better off getting a BEC on a roll at a nearby deli
Mediocre
We got vegetarian food to go and as well as the staff and atmosphere being nice, the food had incredible tastes and ingredients that made it all worth the price!
Amazing food

This place is a real hidden 💎 gem in Brooklyn! Very friendly staff and a cozy atmosphere welcomes you as if you are invited to a friend's house. I've tried both lunch and dinner there and guys, you can't miss out on fried chicken sandwich!!!!!! Just try it. It's damn good. Also, if you are visiting for dinner: I highly recommend their fish (forgot the name of it. Branzino..?) dish and the saffron veggies. Chef knows how to cook! 100% recommeneded!!!
This is a small coffee shop, cafeteria style serving. Not a food place. Pics of food look a lot better than real life. Eggs came out hard when ordered over easy. Employees are pretentious.

I came to this place about 2 years ago and it was amazing. Not sure if they changed the cook, or are just getting a little lazy. The menu is no longer interesting and the apothicary of unique spice/food combinations is no longer thoughtful nor complex. The eggplant dish even used Japanese eggplant... Friday, when I came, it was crowded, and feels overpriced...

Fantastic food & coffee.  Amazing local spot but worth traveling to.

I had a really mediocre experience here. Ordered scrambled eggs and a raspberry cheese danish on a weekend afternoon. The danish was small but I didn't finish it because it was dense on the bottom. The eggs took forever to come out (it wasn't busy) and were bland enough that I actively sought out salt, which I never do.
Best Egg Sandwich I ever had!!👌👌👌👌👌

This place is tiny with a few equally tiny tables but as my friend pointed out, it’s quite photogenic. Very nice decor details. You order your items and pay for everything at the counter and then find a table.  That being said, while the dishes were very prettily presented, they lacked seasoning. This, especially for a bunch of Middle Eastern brunch items. I just wanted some more tinge and spice in the cauliflower since it was so beautifully colourful.
Amazing pastries

Golda is my favorite quick breakfast spot. I normally order to go, and generally can't help myself from stopping if I am walking by in the morning. The egg sandwich is delish, and the coffee is strong. I've tried some pastries, and they're always solid, but I keep going back to the egg sandwich!
Nice coffee and foods.
The egg sandwich was amazing!! Totally recommended. FYI there is no WiFi

One of the best coffee and breakfast/lunch spots in the area!  The coffee is phenomenal - the pastries are homemade and typically have unique flavor combinations. Food is high quality and they use fresh ingredients. The space itself is beautifully designed - fresh and light filled.  Highly recommend to anyone!!
Food was ok, but could have been more flavourful.  People were very friendly.  We did not try any of the pastries or coffees, so those may be better.

I loved the Restaurant, it had nice atmosphere and the food was definitely delicious. When you get there try to get their cheese Danish. Personally it was better than the rest. I got the breakfast sandwich and my gf got some eggplant with eggs and bread. It was pretty tasty. The breakfast sandwich was tasty and it did fill me up to be honest.
This is a great little cafe! Great service, great food!!

Adore this place. A neighborhood gem. Tiny as hell but full of heart. Food excellent. Kudos to chef Kenji.
Cute. Love this place. Also.. best gf muffins and almond milk lattes!!!

Love this place. So close to my house which is amazing. I have tried a few items from here. I always come back for the egg sandwich. Plus their pastries are also really amazing

Food made fresh with love. Not much seating but usually people are in and out quickly. They have vegan friendly cafe drink substites as well.

One of the best food experiences I’ve had in a long time. Thoughtful and delicious food. High level of execution but unpretentious. A real breath of quality fresh air. Highly recommended. I hear that dinner service is starting soon and am very excited to check it out again.

Visited Golda kitchen last week for a brunch ! And I must say my experience was highly satisfactory! I love love love this place ,  small place but big menu. I love their cute decoration with plants and seating arrangements! We ordered sandwiches and their cookie cappuccino! Hands down one of the best sandwiches I've had. I never tried the cookie cappuccino before , but this place serves amazing cookie cappuccino. I will say the staff was friendly and service was amazing. From the food to the service to the design of the coffee mugs , everything was great. I highly recommend this place if you're looking for delicious food that satisfies your stomach and wallet. Love this place and can't wait to be back to try out something else from the menu. ❤️👌🏼 #LetsGuide
Fresh and delicious, very nicely lit place

Simple and nice little place with an egg sandwich to die for. The sauce on the sandwich was full of flavor, the eggs soft and fluffy. I will have to come back to try other things on the menu soon.

Beautiful small intimate cafe - Ash goat cheese is a must, best option on the menu hands down. Their signature eggplant dish is okaY - a little to wet for my taste, missing on the salt and pepper as well as some extra kick. The coffee drinks are spot on - delicious! That if you are lucky to encounter barista John on bar, if not, you are going to need luck for the perfect drink otherwise it is just going to be just okay. Best cafe in the area FORESURE!!!!
Iced coffee here is not good...
Great food and cute place with friendly staff!
Best chocolate banana muffin I’ve had in the city so far.
(Translated by Google) The taste and food in the store was very nice!  (Original) 店内のセンスやお料理、とても素晴らしいお店でした！

So excellent, truly. Very dedicated to their coffee with mindful preparation, amazing ceramics from a local producer, and such a pleasant and thoughtful design. Very high attention to detail, a place for community and conversations. I didn't even try their food offerings which looked stellar, people eating next to me had effusive praise. The owner is hands on. So pleased!

The chicken sandwhich is singularly interesting, flavorful and worth repeat visits. The impossible burger is the famed but seldom seen all-vegetarian mix pioneered by the Bill and Melinda Gates foundation- delicious and worth a try, even for carnivores. Word to the wise, Golda is still waiting on an alcohol license so grab a drink at Doris beforehand.
What a gem. The food is great, inventive, and beautifully plated. The pastries are outstanding too.
Exceptional food, coffee, and pastry. To top it off: the BEST hospitality!

This place is a gem. Amazing, gorgeous food that is somehow simultaneously imaginative and comforting. And the staff is warm and friendly. Don’t go here. I want to keep it all to myself.
Amazing for breakfast
Great food!

Wonderful, inventive breakfast menu that changes regularly. Great coffee. Gets crowded in peak hours. Portions are on the smaller size, especially for the price. Expect to want to finish up with a (delicious) pastry.

One of the best food experiences I’ve had in a long time. Thoughtful and delicious food. High level of execution but unpretentious. A real breath of quality fresh air. Highly recommended. I hear that dinner service is starting soon and am very excited to check it out again.

Egg sandwiches are delish! Beautiful friendly staff. Pumpkin muffins are tasty too!! Very clean. Close to transit. Awesome spot

Part of the new "all day cafe" scene in Brooklyn -- the egg sandwich was highly touted, but I thought it was just messy. Eggs were slightly overdone, with beef bacon that was too chewy, and the sandwich had a lot more going on the it needed. The coffee was totally fine, and I would drink it again.

Healthy delicious fare with a Middle Eastern tinge and good shots of Parlor Coffee and guest roasters in an attractive small space designed by MP Shift. Love the eggplant menemen, everything avocado, oatmeal w/ freekah.

Golda is insanely good! Everything they sell is beautiful, flavorful, and well portioned. I highly recommend their egg sandwich. The owner works the register and oversees everything that goes on so quality is unmatched. I just wish there was more seating because this place gets busy! One of my favorite breakfast spots in Brooklyn and maybe even all of NYC. Highly recommend!

Golda is great! The service is great, the coffee is amazing and the menu is so different and delicious. The types of pastries rotate every few days so it's always a new experience walking in there. The interior is also super cool. Lots of plants and tiles, which gives it a very clean and cool vibe. I love coming here.
A+ all the way around. highly recommended

High quality and tasty food. I recommend the eggplant dish. The almond chai latte is one of the top drinks I've had. And the staff is helpful and so friendly. Do yourself a favor and go try something!
Amazing food and great atmosphere. The owner, Danny, is great!

Great service, thoughtful menu, and everything we had was delicious! Everything is made in house. Food is dynamite and the pastries are all creative interpretations and A+. Worth a trip for this special experience of a thoughtful menu with flavors that you don't get very often.

Danny and his team at Golda are the absolute best! Great service, food is outstanding, and the coffee... The coffee (Parlor AND Heart) they brew is out of this world. You're missing out if you haven't checked out Golda yet.

Usually you walk into a cafe and it's tense, but as soon as I walked into here I had this feeling of relief. Golda is refreshing and Danny made sure to make you feel welcome. I ordered an ice latte and this exotic charred eggplant danish, it was fantastic! I will definitely be returning. Get the cup of coffee ready for me Danny!!

Golda is a brand new cafe that pays attention to the details. It is wonderfully furnished, and the cold brew is delicious. Also, they have incredible baked goods that are made fresh in-house. Welcome to the neighborhood!
Super friendly owner, interesting menu, bright and airy feel, and great food! Wonderful addition to the neighborhood.
